“I am very grateful to Madona Strazda at the University of Latvia, whose dream I had the honor to grant today. I am very happy to see that we already have customers on the floor today,” said Jones. “The constant support of Euroapotheca has helped us to allocate necessary resources to create a successful product. We were also interested in the choice of floor broker at BALTIC FUTURE made by Milda Freimane. She was very pleased to lean on the growth of Latvian companies and entrepreneurship, and we can add that we are no longer merely a contracting room – we are the heart of business on the Baltic States! Whenever you address us, you will be assured prompt and professional help. In the whole region, we proudly say: This is the first real stock exchange! I wish all the best to the company and the shareholders – in the coming 20 years may you continue to be a house for sale and traded securities!” he said.
